# NUC Homelab Environment Configuration
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# The .env file is gitignored and will not be committed.
# Run `just init` for an interactive setup wizard that populates this automatically.

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NUC Connection Details
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# NUC_HOST: Tailscale hostname or IP address of your NUC
# This is used by deploy.sh to connect to the running NUC
# Examples:
#   NUC_HOST=nuc.tail12345.ts.net    # Tailscale MagicDNS (recommended)
#   NUC_HOST=192.168.1.50            # Static LAN IP
#   NUC_HOST=nuc.local               # mDNS (if using Avahi)
NUC_HOST=nuc.tail12345.ts.net

# NUC_USER: SSH username on the NUC
# This user must exist on the NUC and have sudo privileges
# The user should be in the 'wheel' group for passwordless sudo (set during NixOS install)
# Default: steven
NUC_USER=steven

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Optional: Deployment Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# NUC_REMOTE_PATH: Where the homelab configs are deployed on the NUC
# The deploy.sh script rsyncs files to this location
# Default: /home/$NUC_USER/homelab
# Only change this if you're deploying to a non-standard location
# NUC_REMOTE_PATH=/home/steven/homelab

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# How to use:
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. Run `just init` to populate this file interactively
# 2. Or manually edit the values above
# 3. Run `just doctor` to verify everything is set correctly
# 4. Run `just deploy` to push configs to your NUC
#
# For help: just nuc-help
# Full docs: see SETUP.md and README.md
